SIMPLE: scribble
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scribble
<hw>Scrib"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Scrabble</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Woolen Manuf.)</fld> <def>To card
coarsely; to run through the scribbling machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scribble
<hw>Scrib"ble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Scribbled</conjf> <pr>(-b'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Scribbling</conjf> <pr>(-bl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From
<er>Scribe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To write hastily or carelessly,
without regard to correctness or elegance; <as>as, to <ex>scribble</ex>
a letter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fill or cover with careless or worthless
writing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scribble
<hw>Scrib"ble</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To write without care,
elegance, or value; to scrawl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If Maevius <qex>scribble</qex> in Apollo's spite.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Scribble
<hw>Scrib"ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Hasty or careless writing; a
writing of little value; a scrawl; <as>as, a hasty
<ex>scribble</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither did I but vacant seasons spend⟦br⟧
In this my <qex>scribble</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribblement</ent>⟦br⟧
